# 🌤 Weather Data Pipeline & Dashboard

## 📌 Project Overview

An end-to-end data engineering project that ingests weather data, processes it using modern data tools, and visualizes insights through an interactive dashboard.

This project demonstrates real-world data engineering workflows including orchestration, transformation, storage, and visualization.

---

## 🧱 Architecture

```
Data Source → Airflow DAG → PostgreSQL → dbt Models → Streamlit Dashboard
```

---

## 📊 Dashboard Preview

<p align="center">
  <img src="assets/dashboard.png" width="800"/>
</p>

---

## 📈 Features

* 📊 Interactive dashboard built with Streamlit
* 🌡 Temperature & humidity trends visualization
* 📌 KPI metrics (avg, max, min)
* 🔍 Date filtering for analysis
* 📉 Rolling averages for trend detection
* 📋 Data table with full dataset view
* 🔗 Scatter plot (temperature vs humidity)

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack

* Apache Airflow → workflow orchestration
* PostgreSQL → data storage
* dbt → data transformation
* Docker → containerization
* Streamlit → dashboard visualization
* Plotly → interactive charts

---

## 🚀 Run Locally

### 1. Start services

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

### 2. Run Streamlit dashboard

```bash
streamlit run streamlit_app.py
```

### 3. Access

* Airflow: http://localhost:8080
* Dashboard: http://localhost:8501

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```
├── dags/                # Airflow DAGs
├── weather_dbt/         # dbt models
├── assets/              # dashboard images
├── streamlit_app.py     # dashboard app
├── docker-compose.yml   # services setup
└── README.md
```

